{
  "stem": "20021.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Out of those, probably majority, the vast majority registered to go back to Hitler.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Now, that sounds very strange, but there is two explanations for that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "One, as I said before, nobody ever managed to leave Russia, so you had a choice to accept the fact that you'll forever live in Russia or else go back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And interestingly enough, again nobody in his faintest imagination imagined that there will be ever a Holocaust like happened later in Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Going back to Germany meant to suffer for two years as a slave laborer and the war will finish sooner or later.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we together with nearly a million people choose that option and register to go back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was all a big lie.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Russians never intended to let us back in Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But next-- in two weeks, they went with those lists to all those people who registered at night, grabbed them, and sent them to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this is how 250,000 Jews from Poland ended up in Russia and saved themselves, because they were shipped away to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they spent the rest of the war safely there in Siberia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We happened to be at that time in a place called Kalusz, which is a little town.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And outside the house where we lived, there was a big haystack.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when we heard that the soldiers-- we almost saw them-- are rounding up a house down the-- down the road, we all ran into that haystack and hid there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we could see the Russian soldiers going through the house with the list, looking for us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they were very lazy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They-- they weren't really very intent on whatever they were doing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were just doing it because they were told to do.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
